  "prompt": "What is Nuclear Insurance Pool?",
  "response": "A Nuclear Insurance Pool is a collective arrangement formed by multiple insurance companies to provide coverage for nuclear risks, which are typically too large and complex for any single insurer to handle. These pools are designed to spread the financial risk associated with nuclear incidents, including accidents, damage, and liability, among a variety of insurers.\n\nThe pool functions by each member contributing a portion of the total insurance coverage required. This collaboration allows for greater capacity to underwrite policies and ensures that sufficient funds are available in the event of a nuclear incident. Nuclear Insurance Pools are often established at a national level and may be regulated by government authorities to ensure compliance with safety standards and financial security.\n\nThe primary goal of these pools is to provide adequate insurance for nuclear facilities, operators, and contractors, facilitating the development and operation of nuclear energy projects while managing the associated financial risks.",
